        "translationEn": "And who is more unjust than one who invents a lie about Allah or says, \"It has been inspired to me,\" while nothing has been inspired to him, and one who says, \"I will reveal [something] like what Allah revealed.\" And if you could but see when the wrongdoers are in the overwhelming pangs of death while the angels extend their hands, [saying], \"Discharge your souls! Today you will be awarded the punishment of [extreme] humiliation for what you used to say against Allah other than the truth and [that] you were, toward His verses, being arrogant.\"",
